= Prompt Architecture V2 =

{{info}}
**Target Governance Reference** - V2 treats prompts, model routing, config, cache keys, and structured outputs as first-class architecture.

This page documents the target architecture only. It does not approve prompt text changes.
{{/info}}

== Overview ==

{{include reference="FactHarbor.Product Development.Diagrams.V2 Prompt Architecture.WebHome"/}}

== Prompt Registry ==

Every V2 analysis prompt section must have:

* registered owner
* semantic task
* required variables
* output schema
* model task id
* test coverage
* prompt/content hash visibility where needed for reproducibility

Prompt frontmatter variables must match rendered variables. Required-section render warnings should fail contract tests. Orphan sections remain quarantined until a real V2 caller is proven.

V2 prompts must be newly specified. Existing V1 prompt files, profiles, and sections may be read as historical design input during review, but they must not be reused, copied, or loaded by V2 execution. Any prompt-backed V2 task needs its own V2 profile, section id, required-variable contract, output schema, approval record, and tests.

== Model Policy ==

One model task registry owns:

* provider preference
* model tier
* temperature profile
* token budget
* timeout
* retry and fallback policy
* output schema version

Provider fallback is structural resilience. It must not silently change prompt/task semantics.

== Config Snapshot ==

Analysis-affecting tunables belong in UCM/JSON defaults unless explicitly classified as structural constants. TypeScript schemas and JSON defaults must stay synchronized. Dead or weakly wired knobs should fail a config contract test.

Hardcoded analysis-affecting temperatures, thresholds, token budgets, and timeouts are not allowed unless approved as fixed structural constants.

== Cache Governance ==

Any cache key that can affect analysis output must include:

* prompt section name and prompt content hash
* model task id, provider, model, temperature profile, and output schema version
* config snapshot hash and result schema version
* source/evidence identity when evidence is part of the task
* language/search context where it affects retrieval or interpretation
* current-date bucket when the task reasons about current facts
* compatibility adapter version when cached output feeds public projection

Cache reuse for structurally identical inputs is allowed. Cache reuse for semantically equivalent but textually different inputs is allowed only if equivalence is LLM-owned or structurally proven by stable IDs.

== Prompt Genericity and Multilingual Gate ==

Before any V2 prompt migration or cutover:

* no analysis prompt may include Captain validation input terms as examples;
* no prompt may steer by concrete date periods, regions, people, or topic vocabulary unless it is an input variable or provider-facing search query;
* prompt variable rendering must be warning-free for every required section;
* multilingual behavior must be source-language-first and must not force English analysis fallback;
* LLM Expert review and explicit Captain approval are required for actual prompt text edits.

== Quarantine Before Execution ==

The implementation plan must classify these surfaces before prompt-backed V2 execution:

|= Surface |= Required disposition
| ##CLAIM_GROUPING## prompt section | Quarantine or assign real V2 caller with tests.
| ##model-tiering.ts## vs active model resolver behavior | Decide one authority.
| legacy model tier aliases and ##orchestrated## profile usage | Remove, quarantine, or map explicitly.
| duplicate or weakly wired config knobs | Fail contract tests until resolved.
| hardcoded call-site temperatures and budgets | Move to model policy or classify as structural constants.

== Current Blocker ==

Slice 6B, prompt-backed Claim Understanding execution, is blocked until Captain approval and LLM Expert review. Until then, V2 gateway policies remain static/non-executable and V2 analysis output remains a damaged shadow envelope.

Boundary enforcement is expected before prompt-backed execution: analyzer-v2 source must fail tests if it imports V1 analyzer modules, references legacy prompt profiles/files in prompt-loading contexts, or exposes V1-shaped contracts as V2 internals.

